@startuml
title Patron Observer - Historial automatico de pedidos

skinparam shadowing false
skinparam linetype ortho
skinparam defaultFontName Arial

actor "Usuario/Admin" as User

participant "Vista/Admin/Shell" as Client
participant "Order\n(models.Model)" as Order
participant "Django Signals\npre_save/post_save" as Signals
participant "capture_previous_order_state()" as PreSave
participant "create_order_status_history()" as PostSave
database "OrderStatusHistory" as History

User -> Client : crea o actualiza pedido
Client -> Order : save()
Order -> Signals : emite pre_save
Signals -> PreSave : notifica cambio pendiente
PreSave -> Order : consulta estado anterior
Order -> Signals : emite post_save
Signals -> PostSave : notifica pedido guardado
PostSave -> History : crea registro si cambio estado/pago

note right of Signals
GoF Observer:
Django actua como sujeto/event bus
y las funciones receiver son observadores.
end note

note bottom of PostSave
La auditoria queda desacoplada de las vistas:
tambien funciona desde admin, shell o tests.
end note

@enduml
